				<li id="16793068" class="cmnt-root" data="0" data-d="1667352896000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578206/Comet-Azur" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">01 Nov 2022 21:34</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16793068" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I totally think its valid to play From games on easy mode as a way to quickly progress through the game and experience the story as fast as you want. That said, Comet Azur aint it. Its  overrated as a game breaking spell. I heard about how powerful this spell was and it was sold in so many YT videos as a boss melter that was available early game. However, the INT requirement is ridiculously high and the slow cast time/nonexistent tracking render it almost useless in PvE and PvP unless you stack various buffs. I only found it useful for Malenias second phase and Commander Niall. Im probably gonna do a rebirth on my INT build because the stat investment isnt really worth it imo, especially if youre focusing your build around using this as early as possible. Youll quickly become a glass cannon with particularly bad aim. I had much better luck with dragonmaw on a more well-rounded build. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16793068" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16793068" class="cmt-rep